Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo's historic scoring streak of 27 consecutive games with 20 or more points on at least 50% shooting from the field came to an end
Post-Match Reflections: The Bucks' dominant win highlighted the team's depth and ability to perform collectively, with Damian Lillard finding his rhythm, Bobby Portis contributing off the bench, and the Bucks excelling from beyond the arc
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks overwhelmed Toronto early, building a double-digit lead in the first quarter and maintaining control for the rest of the game
Milwaukee knocked down 22 three-pointers while shooting 50% from beyond the arc
The Bucks' offense was dominant, tallying 37 assists as a team and ensuring a balanced scoring effort across the roster
Others: Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded a triple-double, finishing with 11 points, 13 assists, and 12 rebounds
The Bucks improved to 18-16 on the season, now sitting fifth in the Eastern Conference standings
